*   **Digital Twin**: The working group will review the "SDF modeling for digital twin" draft, focusing on its role in demonstrating how to use SDF for digital twin information modeling, ahead of a potential call for adoption. Ari Keränen will drop an email to the list regarding `SDF relation` shortcomings for digital twins.
*   **NIPY**:
    *   A NIPY hackathon will be held in Madrid.
    *   Bart van der Poel will create a new issue to track discussion of `content-format` in NIPY API and SDF examples.
    *   Bart van der Poel will provide a one-sentence summary for each closed issue on the mailing list for historical record.
    *   Rohit will update the draft text to fully remove references to `embedded protocol mapping`.
    *   Issue #98 (Get ID Property Read All / Device-Model Linkage) remains open for further discussion.
    *   A virtual interim meeting is scheduled for July 2nd to continue reviewing remaining NIPY issues.

